#
# Positional: <file> (input file if --input not given)
#
# ttc-converter is an Idris 2 utility for
# converting TTC files (Idris 2's serialized
# typechecker output format) to JSON for
# inspection.  Authored by spcfox (1 GH star).
# Sister tools: idris2 (Idris 2 compiler, in
# corpus as `_idris2`), idris2-pack (Idris 2
# package manager, binary `pack` in corpus).
# Idris 2 TTC files are binary intermediate
# representations stored alongside .idr source
# files; this tool exposes their internals for
# debugging compiler issues.
#
# Critical extraction note: ttc-converter uses
# **Idris 2 `System.GetOpts` library** at
# CommandLine.idr:7 ‚Äî corpus's **first documented
# Idris 2 CLI library**.  `System.GetOpts` is from
# the idris-community/idris2-getopts package (3 GH
# stars; maintained by stefan-hoeck) ‚Äî a port of
# Haskell's `System.Console.GetOpt` to Idris 2.
# Distinct from R270 Haskell `optparse-applicative`
# (newer applicative-style library), R270 Haskell
# `System.Console.GetOpt` (the ORIGINAL ‚Äî Idris 2
# port preserves the API), R309 SML stdlib GetOpt
# (different language port of the same library).
# Sister-libraries: HuwCampbell/optparse-idris
# (port of optparse-applicative to Idris 1).
# Extends cross-language CLI taxonomy to FIFTY-TWO
# library variants: Rust (6), Go (4), Python (3),
# Crystal 1 OptionParser (R269), Haskell (R270),
# OCaml (R271), C (R272), Java (R276),
# Kotlin (R277), Scala (R278), Dart (R279),
# Ruby (R280), Perl (R281), PHP (R282),
# Swift (R283), F# (R284), Lua (R285), C# (R286),
# Nim 1 parseopt (R287), Zig (R288), D (R289),
# Racket (R290), Common Lisp 1 (R291),
# Erlang (R292), Tcl (R293), Pharo Smalltalk (R294),
# Common Lisp 2 clingon (R295), Julia (R296),
# SWI-Prolog optparse (R297), Pony stdlib cli (R298),
# Crystal 2 Admiral (R299), V stdlib `flag` (R300),
# Nim 2 cligen (R301), Clojure babashka.cli (R302),
# Gleam Glint (R303), Ada GNAT.Command_Line (R304),
# C++ CLI11 (R305), Elixir Optimus (R306), Vala
# GLib.OptionContext (R307), Hare stdlib getopt
# (R308), Standard ML stdlib GetOpt (R309),
# Fortran M_CLI2 (R310), Guile (ice-9 getopt-long)
# (R311), Free Pascal TCustomApplication (R312),
# **Idris 2 System.GetOpts** (R313 ‚Äî NEW).
