# CLI library variants documented.  Idris 2
# joins the taxonomy as the LATEST-GENERATION
# dependently-typed language with a real-world CLI
# library port.
#
# Critical extraction note: ttc-converter uses
# **Idris 2 record-update-with-`:=` and `$=`-
# section CLI pattern** at CommandLine.idr:39-43 ‚Äî
# `applyOption Help = { help := True }` uses Idris
# 2's RECORD-UPDATE syntax:
#   `{field := value}` ‚Üê record-update setting
#                          field to value
#   `{field $= func}`  ‚Üê record-update applying
#                          func to current value
# E.g. `{ erase $= (tag ::) }` cons-prepends `tag`
# onto the existing `erase` list via SECTION
# `(tag ::)` (partial application of cons).
# Distinct from R270 Haskell (record-update via
# `r { field = val }` no `$=`), R309 SML (record-
# update `{record where field = val}` differs),
# R290 Racket (`struct-copy` macro), R305 C++
# CLI11 (direct struct-field mutation).  Idris 2's
# approach: BANG-EQUAL `:=` for SET + DOLLAR-EQUAL
# `$=` for FUNCTION-APPLY-TO-FIELD ‚Äî corpus's
# **first documented `$=`-section record-update CLI
# pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: ttc-converter uses
# **Idris 2 `MkOpt SHORT_CHARS LONG_STRINGS
# (NoArg|ReqArg|OptArg) HELP` 4-arity constructor
# spec** at CommandLine.idr:80-89 ‚Äî each `MkOpt`
# entry has POSITIONAL ARGS:
#   1) `List Char` short flags
#   2) `List String` long flags
#   3) `ArgDescr a` argument shape
#   4) `String` help text
# Distinct from R270 Haskell `Option [Char]
# [String] ArgDescr String` (SAME shape ‚Äî Idris 2
# preserves the Haskell type, just renames Option
# to MkOpt), R309 SML `{short, long, desc, help}`
# (labelled record ‚Äî same fields, different
# syntax), R311 Guile quoted-assoc-list (different
# structure entirely).  Idris 2's approach:
# POSITIONAL CONSTRUCTOR ARGS ‚Äî corpus's **first
# documented Idris-2-constructor-as-option-spec
# CLI pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: ttc-converter uses
# **Idris 2 multi-char-list short flags** at
# CommandLine.idr:81 ‚Äî `MkOpt ['?', 'h'] ["help"]
# (NoArg Help) "Show help"` ‚Äî the FIRST positional
# arg is a LIST OF CHARS.  Both `-?` and `-h`
# map to the `Help` constructor.  Sister to R309
# SML `short = "vV"` (string-of-chars) but Idris 2
# uses EXPLICIT LIST SYNTAX `[...]` rather than a
# string.  Distinct from R304 Ada (one short per
# option), R307 Vala GLib (single char in
# OptionEntry), R308 Hare (single char in tuple),
# R311 Guile (`(single-char #\X)` ‚Äî ONE short).
# Idris 2's approach: TYPED LIST OF CHARS ‚Äî type
# system enforces it's a list, not a string.
# Corpus's **second documented multi-character-
# short-flag pattern (Idris 2 list ‚Äî joins SML
# string)**.
#
# Critical extraction note: ttc-converter uses
# **Idris 2 `getOpt POLICY DESCS ARGS` returning
# `MkResult` 4-record pattern** at CommandLine.idr:
# 100-103 ‚Äî `let (MkResult opts [] [] []) = getOpt
# (ReturnInOrder Input) descs args | _ => pure $
# Left InvalidOptions` destructures the parse
# result into `(opts, positionals, unrecognized,
# errors)`.  The `| _ => ...` is Idris 2's IF-
# PATTERN-MATCH-FAILS-CONTINUE syntax ‚Äî if the
# destructure doesn't match exactly, execute the
# fallback.  Distinct from R270 Haskell (similar
# but uses CASE-OF), R309 SML (tuple pattern
# match), R311 Guile (alist accessor `option-ref`).
# Idris 2's approach: PATTERN-MATCH-DESTRUCTURE-
# WITH-FALLBACK ‚Äî corpus's **first documented
# pattern-match-destructure-with-fallback CLI
# parse-result handling pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: ttc-converter uses
# **Idris 2 `ReturnInOrder Input` argOrder policy**
# at CommandLine.idr:100 ‚Äî `ReturnInOrder ctor`
# wraps EACH POSITIONAL with the `Input`
# constructor and adds it to the parsed-options
# list (so positionals are INTERLEAVED with flags
# in the returned ADT list).  Tri-state policy
# `Permute | RequireOrder | ReturnInOrder` ‚Äî SAME
# tri-state as R309 SML GetOpt and R270 Haskell
# `System.Console.GetOpt` ‚Äî confirming the
# Haskell‚ÜíSML‚ÜíIdris 2 port lineage.  Distinct from
# R272 C POSIX getopt (only Permute via getopt_long
# default), R304 Ada (Permute only), R307 Vala
# GLib (Permute only ‚Äî no opt-out).  Corpus's
# **third documented tri-state-argOrder-policy CLI
# library (joining R309 SML and R270 Haskell)**.
